The KRL rulesets in this repository function a demo application that manages a blog called the KBlog. 

Sometimes, you can [http://www.windley.com/kblog/#!/ play with KBlog] (posting is disabled). 

See Chapter 12 of [http://www.amazon.com/The-Live-Web-Event-Based-Connections/dp/1133686680 The Live Web] for an explanation. 

Alternately, you can see these blog posts

* [http://www.windley.com/archives/2011/04/event_hierarchies_a_blog_written_in_krl.shtml Event Hierarchies: A Blog Written in KRL]
* [http://www.windley.com/archives/2011/04/kblog_making_the_back_button_work.shtml Blog: Making the Back Button Work]
* [http://www.windley.com/archives/2011/04/tweeting_from_kblog_thoughts_about_loose_coupling.shtml  Tweeting from KBlog: An Experiment in Loose Coupling]
